<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<body>
	<style>
	.font_1 {
		background-color: black;
		color: yellow;
		font-size: large;
	}
	.font_2 {
		background-color: darkblue;
		color: white;
		font-size: medium;
	}
	.minimal {
		background-color:cornsilk;
		color:darkolivegreen;
		font-family:lucida handwriting;
		font-weight: lighter;
		font-size: large;
	}
	</style>
	<h2 class="font_1">This h2 element is styled per class attribute font_1</h2>
	<h3 class="font_2">This h3 element is styled per class attribute font_2</h3>
	<h4 class="font_1">Even though this is an h4 element, it is styled the same as the h2 element 
	because we pointed to the class attribute font_1</h4>
	<h1 class="minimal">Here is some text styled in my personally created class attribute 'minimal'.</h1>
	<p class="minimal"> So do all who who live to see such times, but it is not for them to decide. It is for them to decide what to do with the time given"</p>
	</body>
</html>